<Requirements version="1" hierarchy="LLR">
  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Start Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall start autonomous exploration when commanded by the main control module and shall initialize the exploration state by setting the current cell as the start cell, marking it as free, and initializing all other cells of the maze as unknown.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Strategy Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall select and execute a deterministic grid-based cell exploration strategy (e.g. depth-first search with backtracking or breadth-first search), operating on the internal maze representation, such that all reachable free cells are visited while avoiding blocked cells.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier Cell Identification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-ENV-1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall periodically identify frontier cells as free cells that have at least one unknown adjacent cell, and shall use this information to drive the exploration strategy until no frontier cells remain reachable.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Termination Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.1.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall terminate exploration when either no reachable frontier cells remain in the map or the exploration time budget defined by the time constraint is exhausted and shall signal completion to the run control module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Motion Commanding</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.4</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall translate exploration decisions into discrete motion commands by issuing motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) calls that move the robot between centers of adjacent cells or rotate it in place by 90 degrees, while respecting the speed limits and wall avoidance constraints.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Front Distance Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall obtain the current front obstacle distance by periodically calling ultrasonic_get_distance(), interpreting the returned float value as the distance to the nearest front obstacle in centimeters.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Obstacle Status Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall periodically read the left and right infrared obstacle sensor statuses by calling infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status(), interpreting the returned uint8_t values as binary obstacle detection flags.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Proximity Estimation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall estimate the presence of walls in front or at the front-left and front-right by combining ultrasonic distance measurements with the binary infrared detections, taking into account the ±2 cm ultrasonic accuracy, approximately 4 cm IR detection range, and approximately 25 degree IR sensor orientation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Collision Avoidance Control</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall ensure that when an estimated wall is within a configurable safety distance in front or at the sides, motor_set commands are adjusted or overridden to reduce speed or stop and steer the robot away such that the robot does not collide with walls.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Blocked Direction Determination</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-ENV-1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall determine for each of the four cardinal movement directions relative to the current cell whether the path is blocked by a wall based on processed sensor data and shall expose this as a boolean blocked/free flag per direction to the mapping module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Data Structure</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall maintain an internal 4x8 grid map data structure where each cell stores its classification state and wall presence information for its four borders, using the maze cell dimensions and wall thickness as assumptions for spatial consistency.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Pose to Cell Association</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall associate the robot pose with a discrete maze cell index and orientation by assuming the robot moves between cell centers along orthogonal directions with step lengths approximately equal to the maze cell dimensions.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Map Update</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.5</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall update the internal map after each cell visit by marking the presence or absence of walls between the current cell and its adjacent cells in the cardinal directions based on the blocked direction information.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Static Environment Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall assume that once a wall or free passage between two cells has been recorded in the internal map, this information remains valid for the entire operation and shall not be removed unless explicitly reset.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Access Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
