  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Start Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall start autonomous exploration when commanded by the main control module through a dedicated exploration_start interface and shall initialize the exploration state by setting the current cell as the start cell, marking it as FREE, and initializing all other cells of the maze as UNKNOWN.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Strategy Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall select and execute a deterministic grid-based cell exploration strategy, such as depth-first search with backtracking or breadth-first search, operating on the internal maze representation, such that all reachable FREE cells are visited while avoiding BLOCKED cells.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier Cell Identification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-ENV-1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall periodically identify frontier cells as FREE cells that have at least one UNKNOWN adjacent cell and shall use this information to drive the exploration strategy until no frontier cells remain reachable.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Termination Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.1.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall terminate exploration when either no reachable frontier cells remain in the map or the exploration time budget is exhausted and shall signal an exploration result status, including success or failure, to the run control module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Motion Commanding</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-1.2.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall translate exploration decisions into discrete motion commands by requesting motion primitives such as forward-cell moves and 90-degree turns from the actuator command abstraction, so that the abstraction issues corresponding motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) calls that move the robot between centers of adjacent cells or rotate it in place by 90 degrees while respecting speed limits and wall avoidance constraints.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Mode State Management</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall maintain a navigation state machine with at least the states IDLE, EXPLORATION, RETURN, and SECOND_RUN and shall only start exploration when in the IDLE state and shall transition from EXPLORATION to RETURN or IDLE according to the exploration result.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.7">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Command Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall expose an exploration_start command and an exploration_stop command to the main control module and shall ignore new exploration_start commands while exploration is active, except for exploration_stop which shall request early termination.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.8">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Unreachable Region Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, at exploration termination, determine whether UNKNOWN cells remain that are not reachable from any FREE cell and shall report an exploration failure result to the main control module if such unreachable UNKNOWN regions exist.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Front Distance Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall obtain the current front obstacle distance by periodically calling ultrasonic_get_distance(), interpreting the returned float value as the distance to the nearest front obstacle in centimeters.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Obstacle Status Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall periodically read the left and right infrared obstacle sensor statuses by calling infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status(), interpreting the returned uint8_t values as binary obstacle detection flags.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Proximity Estimation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall estimate the presence of walls in front and at the front-left and front-right by combining ultrasonic distance measurements with the binary infrared detections, taking into account an approximate ±2 cm ultrasonic accuracy, an infrared detection range of approximately 4 cm, and infrared sensor orientations of approximately 25 degrees relative to the robot front direction.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Collision Avoidance Control</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-1.2.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall ensure that when an estimated wall is within a configurable safety distance in front or at the sides, the motion command arbiter adjusts or overrides requested motion commands to reduce speed, stop, or steer the robot away such that the robot does not collide with walls.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Blocked Direction Determination</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-ENV-1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall determine, for each of the four cardinal movement directions relative to the current cell, whether the path is blocked by a wall based on processed sensor data and shall expose this as a boolean blocked or free flag per direction to the mapping module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Data Structure</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall maintain an internal 4 by 8 grid map data structure where each cell stores its classification state and wall presence information for its four borders, using the maze cell dimensions and wall thickness as assumptions for spatial consistency.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Pose to Cell Association</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall associate the robot pose with a discrete maze cell index and orientation by assuming the robot moves between cell centers along orthogonal directions with step lengths approximately equal to the maze cell dimensions, using calibrated relationships between commanded motion primitives and resulting displacement without assuming constant rotational velocity.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Map Update</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.5</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall update the internal map after each cell visit by marking the presence or absence of walls between the current cell and its adjacent cells in the cardinal directions based on the blocked-direction information.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Static Environment Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall assume that once a wall or free passage between two cells has been recorded in the internal map, this information remains valid for the entire operation and shall not be removed unless the map is explicitly reset.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Access Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall provide an interface for other modules to query the map for cell classification, wall presence between cells, and adjacency relations using cell indices and cardinal directions.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell State Representation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall represent each maze cell state as one of three values: FREE, BLOCKED, or UNKNOWN, and shall store this classification in the internal map data structure.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.4.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Free Cell Classification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.5</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall classify the currently occupied cell as FREE when the robot center is inside the cell and collision avoidance has not been triggered for that cell occupancy interval.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.4.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Blocked Cell and Wall Classification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.5</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall classify directions from a FREE cell that are determined as blocked as having walls between the corresponding cells and shall classify cells beyond impassable walls as BLOCKED when they are not reachable from any FREE cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.4.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Unknown Cell Maintenance</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.1.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall keep the classification of cells as UNKNOWN until sufficient sensor and connectivity information is gathered to classify them as FREE or BLOCKED according to the exploration strategy.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.5.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Mapping Time Budget</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall enforce a mapping time budget of at most 5 minutes from the start of exploration until the exploration termination condition is met or the time budget is exceeded.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.5.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Time Monitoring Mechanism</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.5</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall periodically monitor elapsed exploration time using a system timer and shall trigger exploration termination when the elapsed time reaches 5 minutes.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Planning Graph Construction</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall construct a planning graph whose nodes correspond to FREE cells in the internal map and whose edges connect nodes representing adjacent cells without walls between them.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Cost Definition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall define the cost of a path as the sum of the costs of its edges, where each edge cost is proportional to the distance between cell centers and may include additional penalties for turns or speed limitations to approximate traversal time.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Optimal Path Algorithm</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall compute an optimal path between a given start cell and target cell in the planning graph using a deterministic shortest-path algorithm such as Dijkstra or A* based on the defined path costs.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Path Planning</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-ENV-3.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-1.1.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall select a specific goal cell within the identified 2 by 2 goal region and compute an optimal path from the current robot cell to that goal cell using the planning algorithm.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Representation for Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-1.1.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall represent the computed path as an ordered sequence of cell indices and orientations or as discrete motion primitives, consisting of forward steps and in-place turns, suitable for execution by the motion control module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-1.1.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Planning Service Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall provide a planning service interface that accepts a start cell, a target cell, and an optimization criterion based on path cost and shall return an optimal path or an indication that no path exists.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-1.1.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, after exploration, compute an optimal path from the robot’s current cell to the designated start cell using the internal map and the same planning algorithm as used for goal paths.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-1.2.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall execute the computed return path by submitting the path’s motion primitives to the motion command arbiter, which then issues appropriate motor_set commands for each path segment while continuing to enforce collision avoidance.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return State Transition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.1.6</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall transition the navigation state machine from EXPLORATION to RETURN when exploration is reported as completed and shall transition from RETURN to IDLE when the robot reaches the start cell or when a return failure condition is detected.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Path Retrieval</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-1.1.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-1.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, after returning to the start cell, obtain or recompute the fastest path from the start cell to the selected goal cell within the goal region based on the final map and the defined path cost.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Execution Trigger</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall start the second run from the start cell towards the goal region using the fastest path when the robot is at the start cell, the return-to-start phase is complete, and the fastest path to the goal region has been obtained.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Failure Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-1.2.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.4</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall detect failure conditions during the second run, including persistent collision avoidance interventions that prevent progress or timeout, shall stop the robot, and shall report a second-run failure status to the main control module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fastest Path Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-1.1.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall treat the optimal path used for the second run as the path with minimal estimated traversal time according to the defined path costs and shall not select any alternate path with a higher cost.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>High-Speed Second Run Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-1.2.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall execute the second run along the fastest path by requesting motion primitives at higher translational speeds than used during exploration, while the motion command arbiter enforces configured maximum operational speeds and collision avoidance constraints.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-1.1.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Minimum Clearance Configuration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall configure a minimum clearance distance between the robot’s circular body and maze walls based on the robot diameter and cell dimensions and shall use this threshold when evaluating collision risk.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-1.2.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Noise Filtering</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall apply temporal filtering or averaging to consecutive ultrasonic distance measurements to reduce the effect of ±2 cm sensor noise on wall detection decisions.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-1.2.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Robust Classification Under Uncertainty</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-RELIAB-1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall defer wall and cell classification updates when sensor readings are inconsistent or rapidly fluctuating and shall retain UNKNOWN state until a stable decision can be made.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Acquisition Scheduler</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement a periodic sensor acquisition loop that invokes ultrasonic_get_distance() and the infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status() functions at a fixed or bounded sampling rate suitable for real-time navigation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Data Normalization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall normalize raw sensor readings into a common internal format containing distance estimates and binary obstacle flags annotated with sensor source and orientation metadata.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Actuator Command Abstraction</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall provide an abstraction layer that converts high-level motion commands such as move forward one cell or turn 90 degrees into one or more calls to motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) with appropriate speed values.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Actuator Command Rate Limiting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall limit the rate at which motor_set is called to a defined maximum update frequency to account for non-constant motor rotational speed and to ensure stable control.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Motion Command Arbitration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-1.2.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.2.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-1.3.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement a motion command arbiter that receives motion primitives from exploration, return, and second-run controllers, applies translational speed limits including high-speed second-run settings, allows collision avoidance to override or reduce commands with highest priority, and enforces actuator command rate limiting before issuing motor_set calls.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Error Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall handle invalid or out-of-range values returned by ultrasonic_get_distance by discarding them or replacing them with the last valid measurement and flagging the reading as unreliable.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-INTERF-3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Status Interpretation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-3.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall interpret non-zero values returned by infrared_get_dsl_status and infrared_get_dsr_status as obstacle present and zero as obstacle absent.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-HARDWARE-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Robot Footprint Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall model the robot as a circle with an 11 cm diameter when reasoning about clearance within a 17.2 cm by 17.2 cm cell to ensure the robot can traverse corridors without collision.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-HARDWARE-2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Differential Drive Commanding</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall control the differential drive robot by issuing motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) commands with integer values between 0 and 100 for each wheel to achieve forward motion, backward motion, and in-place rotation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-HARDWARE-2.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Odometry-Free Motion Estimation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall estimate cell-to-cell movements and 90-degree rotations based on commanded motor_set durations and speeds without assuming a constant rotational velocity and may use calibration constants to map command durations to approximate displacements.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-HARDWARE-2.2.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Rotational Speed Independence</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall not rely on the robot wheels spinning at constant rotational speed for a given motor_set command and shall design motion control to tolerate variations in wheel speed.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-HARDWARE-2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Translational Speed Limits</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-HARDWARE-2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-HARDWARE-2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall map commanded motor_set speed values in the range 0 to 100 to translational speeds between 0 cm/s and approximately 200 cm/s and shall enforce a configurable upper limit on commanded speeds during operation that does not exceed 200 cm/s to reduce collision risk.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-ENV-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Maze Grid Indexing</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall index the maze as a fixed 4 by 8 grid of cells using integer coordinates or indices and shall restrict all map and planning operations to this grid.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-ENV-1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Geometry Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall assume that all maze cells are square with side length approximately 17.2 cm and shall use this dimension when estimating distances between cell centers.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-ENV-1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Thickness Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall assume that walls between cells have a uniform thickness of approximately 1.6 cm and shall consider this when reasoning about robot clearance at cell boundaries.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-ENV-1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Intercell Wall Representation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall represent walls only along the borders shared by adjacent cells in the grid and shall not represent walls inside a single cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-ENV-2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Static Map Update Policy</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.4</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall not remove or time-out wall information once recorded in the map and shall treat any subsequent contradictory measurement as sensor noise to be filtered.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-ENV-3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Identification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-ENV-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall identify as the maze goal region any contiguous 2 by 2 block of cells that are all classified as FREE and enclosed by walls or maze boundaries as specified in the environment model.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>
</Requirements>
